  "evidence_sources": {
    "M1": {
      "locator": "full.md # 3.1 试验概况",
      "type": "materials_loading_context",
      "notes": [
        "The paper reports 22 circular HSCFST standard specimens in 9 confining-ratio groups under axial compression.",
        "Steel yield strengths were measured by standard tensile tests; concrete was naturally cured with the specimens under the same conditions.",
        "The concrete strength used in the specimen tables is fck=53.4 MPa, converted from fcu=76.8 MPa cube strength.",
        "Specimens were designed with L/D about 3, filled after one end plate was welded, levelled with cement mortar after about 20 days of curing, and closed with the other end plate.",
        "Tests used flat-plate hinges at both ends and a 500 t hydraulic compression machine with monotonic incremental loading."
      ]
    },
    "T1": {
      "locator": "full.md 表1; images/表1钢管高强混凝土的试件参数.png",
      "type": "specimen_geometry_materials",
      "notes": [
        "Table 1 gives specimen labels, D x t x L in mm, steel fy, concrete fck, confining ratio xi, and load-deformation curve feature.",
        "HSC1 has no descending branch; HSC2 through HSC9 are reported with descending branches.",
        "Visual/PDF confirmation was used for tightly spaced decimals and the bottom HSC9 row; HSC2 diameter is read as 115.9 mm, consistent with the L/D design statement and xi value."
      ]
    },
    "T2": {
      "locator": "full.md 表2; images/表2轴压强度承载力计算和实测值比较.png",
      "type": "capacity_results",
      "notes": [
        "Only rows whose data source is 本文 were retained; literature-comparison rows from references were excluded.",
        "For a group with multiple specimens, the footnote states Nue is the average measured bearing capacity.",
        "The retained measured capacities are the reported Nue values in kN for HSC1 through HSC9."
      ]
    },
    "M2": {
      "locator": "full.md # 3.1 试验概况, paragraphs after 表1",
      "type": "condition_context",
      "notes": [
        "Narrative notes HSC4-1 and HSC4-2 did not capture the full descending branch because the straight weld seam ruptured after ultimate load."
      ]
    }
  },
